{
  "texts": [
    "But for NLP tasks in other languages, the BERT model is not competent.",
    "In paper [16,18,24,26], other language models based on the BERT model have been established.",
    "Among them, paper [16] trained a large number of Dutch corpus to obtain a Rob-BERT model based on Dutch, and paper [18] established an ALBERTo model for Italian NLP tasks.",
    "These two models perform very well in the NLP task of the corresponding language.",
    "Since Korean is one of the rich languages that use non-Latin alphabets and lack resources, it is also important to capture language-specific linguistic phenomena."
  ]
}